      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LEAVING LAS VEGAS (1) finished seventh over 1200m at Belmont Park at his most recent appearance on March 4. This is a little easier today and he has placed 3/4 when fresh in the past. Looks well placed today and can land the knockout blow. ACES TO WIN (5) returned from a spell two weeks ago when he was beaten 3 lengths into fifth over 1200m at this track. Fitter this time. Hard to beat in this suitable race. SCHUHBECK (8) came home strongly last start to finish second, beaten 0.7 lengths, over 1200m at this track. Among the better chances. SPIRIT OF LUNA (7) has not won for a long while. Last raced on April 19 when beaten 5 lengths into sixth at Geraldton over 1605m. Likely improver who should be about the money. HARRIS ROAD (4) is next best.",
